issue.title: Fix build for wasm
issue.body:
Adds necessary \#ifs to fix the WASM build.

### Motivation:

Seems like a few places were missed in the locking refactor, which made the WASM build fail due to missing pthread types and unknown `rwlock` variable.

### Modifications:

\#if-ed out remaining mentions of pthread types and variables not available on WASM.

### Result:

`swift-log` is usable on WASM again.

issue.body:

The change has been verified on a custom Linux armv7 system. Cross-compilation was used for the armv7 build, so I wasn't able to run the tests for that, but all tests pass on x86_64.

issue.title: Fix build for wasm
issue.body:
Adds necessary \#ifs to fix the WASM build.

### Motivation:

Seems like a few places were missed in the locking refactor, which made the WASM build fail due to missing pthread types and unknown `rwlock` variable.

### Modifications:

\#if-ed out remaining mentions of pthread types and variables not available on WASM.

### Result:

`swift-log` is usable on WASM again.

Seems like a few places were missed in the locking refactor, which made the WASM build fail due to missing pthread types and unknown `rwlock` variable.

### Modifications:

\#if-ed out remaining mentions of pthread types and variables not available on WASM.

### Result:

`swift-log` is usable on WASM again.
